 ?<br><br>Granted EQ will never have these kinds of things, and starting over when you have a extremely high level character wouldn't be appealing.  However is a thief basically the class a lot of people were actually looking for and rogue was just the closest thing EQ had ?  <br><br>This is not a flame in any way shape or form, as I find EQ to be a great game ( even if it gets aggravating at times ).  Please feel free to disagree, add, or change any of the ideas that were thought of up there.  For those that are table-top RPG game fans, the games in question I got the comparsions from were Dungeons and Dragons, Rolemaster, and Palladium. <p><img src="http://www.twilite.org/~chrome/images/sigs/larcensig.jpg" border="0"><BR>Larcen Mistwalker <BR>Assassin of Amity<BR><BR>Love is the greatest treasure</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=myndrall>myndrall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 1:20:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22289.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think the class some of us really wanted was a THIEF</span><hr size=1> Well, not to high jack a pretty decent thread, but...<br><br>I dont think i would go for Thief so much as Assassin... i dont just mean the title you get at lvl 60.. I mean an actual assassin, in every respect<br><br>A true lone person, one who does what he/she does for the sole reason of enjoyment of proffesion, and is good at what he does<br><br>A master in the art of poison, But poison that is actually usefull for once, not just some archaic(sp) hobby with almost 0 use after lvl 50, poison's that can crumble a man or beast with a single dose applied to your rapier, or to his meal, not just do 257 DD at lvl 60... <br><br>A master of the sneak attack from behind, but not just with l33t backstabs with the dagger of uberclowness, but also with weapons like a garroet (piano wire) and a bolio for fleeing victems, A person who also knows his victems weak points from the front, so a well placed dagger into a vital organ drops him like a sack of rocks, or a well time hand strike to the neck renders his oppenent useless for the up coming combat<br><br>A person who could get into ANY castle, track any mob in a dungeon, take out his target and slip back out unseen to collect his purse for taking out his mark<br><br>as far as EQ goes, i would gladly give up such useless skills as pick pocket or sense traps for a usefull intimidate, not one that &quot;fears&quot; my oppenent, but freezes him in place as he sees death in my hollow eyes, or to have a &quot;vital strike&quot; from the front postion that acts as DoT for hitting a vital organ, and does not stop till cured or death, nothing huge mind you, just something that proves my skill as a death dealer.. <br><br>I would want use of ropes, poison darts, Illusions that were usefull rather then &quot; cool &quot;<br><br>I would want &quot;jobs&quot; given to me, where my sole purpose was to bribe guards, sneak in, kill my mark, and get back out before breakfast to collect my fee, with out assistance from anyone<br><br>I would gladly give those skills up for the task of being hired to deliver devastating blows to a mob to insure victory, or to weaken it with my poison so that it is a mere shadow of its former self, for a hefty price of course, only to leave the people the left upon payment<br><br>Im sure to some these ideas are silly, and i had more, just didnt feel like typing them, but that is what i would love to be in this game <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nenjindarkeyes>Nenjin Darkeyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 1:41:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22289.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I hear you</span><hr size=1> Ever since I started D&amp;D back in the day, my characters were ALWAYS theives. I started a rogue for this reason.<br>But at about 30 I realized that there isnt enough dynamic content in this for you to do the stuff  you did with your thief in D&amp;D. Its pretty much hack and slash, combat maneuvers. Aside from questing, there really isnt much in EQ that doesnt revolve around combat.<br><br>If VI actually made content where there were lots of traps in regular places, walls that have a reason to be climbed, and languages to be decypherd(sp?)(well they already have that, but no one ever readst those things anyways) I would be all for starting a level 1 Thief. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukuurus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kuurus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 1:51:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22289.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I hear you</span><hr size=1> Actually, I really wanted an Assassin when I created my character.  Thus I made him a semi-warrior when I clicked create back in May of 1999 - put all his points into STR and STA without a clue what stats did.<br><br>I always intended, and wanted to play him as a quick, light warrior opening battles with a backstab to gain an advantage, then fighting toe to toe - being a hitman going after targets using poison etc...Of course these things aren't really feasible, they were even less so at that time...but that's the idea I had in mind when creating my rogue.  He was an Assassin, not a Thief. <p><font size=4><font face=hanzel, verdana, arial black><b>Kuurus</font></b><BR><font size=2><font face=hanzel, verdana, arial black>Assassin and Guild Leader</font><BR><font size=2><font face=hanzel, verdana, arial black><i>Retired</font></i><BR><font size=2><font face=andy, hanzel, arial black><b><A HREF=http://pub52.ezboard.com/bwarcry97210>Cry of War</A></font></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usorinie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sorinie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 1:55:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22289.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I hear you</span><hr size=1> I had kind of the same idea on the INT caster spells idea.<br>You get whatever mana you have for +mana items as your max. and right clicking on any int caster scroll 20 lvls under yours would cast it.  SO at 60th you could cast 40th lvl spells.. (if you had enough +mana gear for the spell) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uevertorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evertorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 1:58:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22289.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/pmelvin14/safehousepic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think the class some of us really wanted was a THIEF</span><hr size=1> Myndrall,<br>I would definatly go for the Assassin, that's the way I play my rogue. <p><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7500>Evertorrn DarkHeart</a> - Level 56 Blackguard <BR>    Evertorn Soul - Level 53 Vicar <BR>    <I>“My Word is my Honor, My Honor is my Life..”</I><BR>    <I>“My blood for your blood..”</I><BR><I>“Strength and Honor..”</I><BR>"<b>We</b> will be <b>perfect</b> in <b>every aspect</b> of the <b>game</b>. You drop a pass...you run a mile, you miss a blocking assignment...you run a mile, you fumble the football...and I will break my foot off in your John Brown hind parts and <u>then</u> you will run a mile. <b>Perfection</b>...it's what I want."</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upyrianawolfteaser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pyriana Wolfteaser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 2:03:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22289.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think the class some of us really wanted was a THIEF</span><hr size=1> I wanted, and have always played, a thief, when I made my rogue, I was essentially forced into it because there's nothing else even remotely like a thief, although if you think about it, from a game mechanics standpoint, a bard is closer to a thief then a rogue is, can escape and hide well, can trick things into doing stuff for them (charm), can distract so that they can do other more important things (mez)...I think they can blind too? I don't know the bard songs very well, but that's my opinion =X <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5151">Pyriana "CR Whore" Wolfteaser</A>, 60th level Assassin...<br>"Doing it best from behind since Nineteen Ninety Nine..."<br><IMG SRC="http://www.pyriana.f2s.com/backstab.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ularcenmistwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Larcen Mistwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 2:10:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22289.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think the class some of us really wanted was a THIEF</span><hr size=1> Wasn't an Assassin a subclass of a thief in D/D also ?  Also, these are excellent responses I've been reading so far.  Keep em coming :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzondro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zondro</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 5:55:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22289.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think the class some of us really wanted was a THIEF</span><hr size=1> I thought of an excellent way to may a rogue closer to a thief, with a new weapon<br><br>Dirk of the great thief<br>2h piercing<br>DMG 30, delay 20<br>AC -200<br>Piercing -100%<br>effect: Evade  (lower, or remove from hate list)<br>Rogue/all<br><br>This way a rogue could lose basically all melee output, for HUGE backstabs.  might be cool :) <p><img src = "http://www.mnickey.com/zon_sig.gif"><br>-Zondro Devvildoll<br>60  GWarlock of Karana<br>"VERY BAD!!!!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uredniwrah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Redniwrah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 7:09:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22289.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think the class some of us really wanted was a THIEF</span><hr size=1> DISTRACTION:<br>Target an enemy and Click your distraction skill this will cause mob to either move away to investigate from its position or turn around facing a random direction.<br><br>This will then allow the thief to sneak in or if the back of the mob is facing the assasin... heh.<br><br>When used in combat this will cause mobs to get confused (making the mob more vulnerable), for a few sec or until the next hit.<br><br>SWINDLE<br>Used on Merchant NPC so that the thief can sell items to them at a higher price. Basically just temporarily increases faction of the Merchant with you. Maybe (randomly) later once the effect wears off, you will lose faction form what it was originally. ie the if Merchant realise he was cheated.<br><br>SPRINT<br>Allows rogues to run off at sow speed for a few secs or till stamina drains. Reuse time maybe like 20-30 min. RL scenario would be like when a thief gets caught stealing so he dashes off to get away from the authority. (yeah similar to DAOC) <br><br>SPELL<br>Maybe simple spell should be good enough. More in the line of causing mishief. Can't think of any yet.<br><br>LEAP:<br>Allows us to jump higher than others.(think ninja)<br><br>STALK /ING<br>Basically target a mob click stalk after that you just follow the mob manually of course. There is a chance that the mob being stalked will realise it is being followed. When you later(certain time limitation) engage the mob you will have a chance to cause insane damage to this specific mob. Basically you been stalking the enemy and know its weak pts so chance to cause more dam. <br><br>This skill should be used in conjunction with distraction to lure a mob to a safe spot to finish off.<br><br>SET TRAPS<br>Basically it should work by placing a trap object on the ground and when a mob walks over it. Dam or effect is dealt to the mob. Of course some mob will be able to detect traps and will be unharmed by the traps.<br><br>CLIMB<br>Wood elfs should get this ). Anyways I don't think it will be implemented. Or that they can make only certain wall scalable.<br><br>Jump -&gt; Backstab<br>To Cause even a higher BS damge. But has a high chance of missing.<br><br>DISGUISE<br>NOT disguise as a different race but a CLASS only. ( just a toy or could be used in certain quests, in PvP servers and to stop people form thinking I am a druid/ranger) <br><br>STRANGULATE<br>With the correct equipment the ability to Strangulate certain mobs but can only be done from behind. If mob have EB capability then it will not work. Mob will lose HP from when this skill is used after they run out of breath. This skill should be affected by STR and also drains the enemy and your stamina. If the rogue str is lower than the mob it will be easily be disrupted.<br><br><br>Will add more later. <br><br>regards,<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uredniwrah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Redniwrah</A> at: 2/15/02 6:43:35 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukelthana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelthana</A></span>