n rare cases, but it's something I'd personally love to have.<br><br>Like I said, this is the biggest problem I have with the rogue class, and I doubt it's going to be changed in this game, it's already too engraved in. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umerristealshearts.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merri Stealshearts</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 7:33:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22289.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think the class some of us really wanted was a THIEF</span><hr size=1> I have always played thieves in roleplay games, but never once has the focus of my &quot;thief&quot; been on actual theft, heh. The thief class, as I defined it to myself, could go two ways: <br><br>1 - ultra-light combat concentrating mainly on missiles and the occasional backstab (definitely not a survivor in melee) who relied on the laying of traps, use of poison, and the skills of larceny (pickpocket and pick-lock) to get by. These types have high agility and dexterity, excellent avoidance, and are limited to light and fast weaponry (piercers and missiles) which can be easily concealed. They have high skill in trap placement and disarming, and are never short of cash, or trouble, and can hide &quot;in the shadows&quot; to avoid detection. This is a typical AD&amp;D thief.<br><br>2 - the ambusher / assassin. Medium combat durability with superlative fighting skills and high damage but relatively low hitpoints. Made to attack fast, do big damage, and get back out of range. Limited to piercing or low-delay slashing weapons, excellent agility and avoidance but limited armor class. Their skills are almost totally weaponry-based and they have a high attack capability but not much defense. Their non-combat abilities are somewhat limited, but they enjoy the same stealth characteristics as thieves. AD&amp;D has called these types &quot;assassins&quot; and &quot;swashbucklers&quot; and even &quot;blademasters&quot;. <br><br>Prior to EQ I played my rogues as assassins: acrobatic, elusive, and devestating in attack, but vulnerable in defense being somewhat frailer than most melee. I have toyed with the thief style somewhat, but when I got into my EQ rogue I found my &quot;home&quot; style pretty much perfectly represented - even if they DID advise putting points into utterly useless stats =/ <p><font size=3><font color=#990033><font face=copperplate gothic light, times new roman, arial>Merribelle Stealshearts</font><BR><font size=2><font face=copperplate gothic light, times new roman, arial>~hench-wench~ <BR><A HREF=http://pub52.ezboard.com/bwarcry97210>Cry of War</A></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udizzykid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dizzy Kid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 8:19:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22289.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dizzykid.homestead.com/files/eyes01.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think the class some of us really wanted was a THIEF</span><hr size=1> Hrmm, in UO, I played a Thief (Nico) and an Assassin (Rulu) type of rogues. I like them both, but I lean towards the Assassin more. I really like the ideas presented by Redniwrah, even though some of them are very DAoCish hehe.<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> SWINDLE<br>Used on Merchant NPC so that the thief can sell items to them at a higher price. Basically just temporarily increases faction of the Merchant with you. Maybe (randomly) later once the effect wears off, you will lose faction form what it was originally. ie the if Merchant realise he was cheated.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>That's cool, but need to have an opposite to that too, for buying stuff. So basically, the exact same thing, but backwards. Not sure what you would call it. =\ &quot;Let's Make a Deal&quot; ehe?<br><br>--DK-- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rorne>Rorne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 9:41:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22289.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think the class some of us really wanted was a THIEF</span><hr size=1> Bah, I want to be a swashbuckler. I hate the whole assassin image. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvinven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vinven</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://raven.tomeofages.com/raven_grey2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/15/02 12:55:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22289.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think the class some of us really wanted was a THIEF</span><hr size=1> Well theres no real way to define it. You can spend some good time working on stealth, pick locks, pockets, traps etc and view yourself as a thief, or be a weaker